NEITHER HERE NOR THERE.Definition: an expression that means 'it does not matter because it is not a relevant point'

STADIUM.Definition: a large closed area of land with rows of seats around the sides and often with no roof, used for sports events and musical performances

TYPICAL.Definition: showing all the characteristics that you would usually expect from a particular group of things

REGARDLESS.Definition: despite; not being affected by something

EXIST.Definition: to be present or be a condition

WEIRD.Definition: very strange and unusual, unexpected, or not natural

'CAUSE.Definition: an informal way of writing the word ‘because’

RIVALS.Definition: a person, group, etc. competing with others for the same thing or in the same area

REAL TALK.Definition: a slang term that refers to when a person speaks candidly without filtering out words that may hurt someone's feelings

HAT TRICK.Definition: an occasion when a player scores three times in the same game, especially in football

SHIT.Definition: an informal way of saying 'stuff' or 'things'

GETTING BACK ON TRACK.Definition: continuing as expected or as planned, particularly after a distraction, issue, or problem

INTENTIONS.Definition: something that someone wants and plans to do

GUNNER.Definition: (in football) player who specializes in running down the sideline very quickly in an attempt to tackle the kick or punt returner

STRENGTHENED.Definition: to make something stronger or more effective, or to become stronger or more effective

CONSISTENCY.Definition: the quality of always happening in a similar way

SURPRISINGLY.Definition: unexpectedly or in a way that is unusual

A FORCE TO BE RECKONED WITH.Definition: a group with a lot of power and influence

WORK OUT.Definition: to happen or develop in a particular way

NOTABLE.Definition: important and deserving attention, because of being very good or interesting

POSSESSION.Definition: (in football) a team keeping hold of the ball for as long as possible to create goal scoring opportunities and prevent the opposition from a posing a threat to a team's goal

DIVERSITY.Definition: the fact of many different types of things or people being included in something; a range of different things or people

ABILITIES.Definition: the physical power or skill needed to do something

GUARANTEED.Definition: sure to happen or be true
